[2] Brazil (Campo Grande)
Date: 28 Feb 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: O Estado de S.Paulo [trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.estadao.com.br/ultimas/cidades/noticias/2007/mar/01/206.htm>

Campo Grande [city] approves law to combat dengue
-----------------------------------------------
The city council of Campo Grande on Thu 1 Mar 2007 approved a law
that will facilitate the combat of dengue, which, since the beginning
of this year [2007] has afflicted 76 of the 78 municipal districts of
Mato Grosso do Sul [state]. In total, 53 146 [dengue] cases were
recorded in the state.
The new law ... obligates property owners to be responsible to
eliminate containers that can accumulate water so that the mosquito
_Aedes aegypti_ (the disease [virus] vector) will not proliferate.
According to the Executive Director of the Municipal Health
Secretariat, Salim Cheade, on Thursday [2 Mar 2007], the city is
facing the largest dengue epidemic in its history, with 27 300 cases
registered, a number greater than was registered in 2002, which
totaled nearly 21 000 cases.
--
