[3] Indonesia
Date: 19 Feb 2007
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: Jakarta Post - Jakarta, Indonesia [edited]
<http://www.thejakartapost.com/detailgeneral.asp?fileid=20070219154844&irec=32>

A total of 2767 Central Java residents contracted dengue fever
between early this year and 16 Feb 2007, with the [numbers of] fatal
victims reaching 73 people, a provincial health official said.
In January 2007, the number of dengue patients in Central Java was
1461, and in February 2007, the figure increased by 1306, the head of
the Central Java provincial health office, Endang Agustinar, said on
Monday [19 Feb 2007].
The dengue outbreaks occurred in 7 districts, namely Blora, Pati,
Jepara, Pekalongan, Semarang, Pemalang, and Batang.
"The incidence of dengue fever is very much related to the rainy
season. It usually increases sharply during the rainy season when
there is a lot of stagnant water where _Aedes aegypti_ mosquitoes can
easily breed," he said.
--
